      • withKeysDomain

        public IntHashConfig withKeysDomain(int minPossibleKey,
                           int maxPossibleKey)
        Returns int hash config with the specified keys domain.

        This is a performance hint, hash containers could, but aren't required to throw IllegalArgumentException on putting key out of the specified domain.

        Example: 

         // only positive keys
 conf = conf.withKeysDomain(1, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        Returns:
        int hash config with the specified keys domain
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if minPossibleKey is greater than maxPossibleKey

      • withKeysDomainComplement

        public IntHashConfig withKeysDomainComplement(int minImpossibleKey,

        Returns int hash config with the specified keys domain complement.

        Example:
